[Reggae Section]

The G chord slams right into an F#m

Chord Progression:

F#m>D>A>E

Besides chords, most of the guitar is effects (Trey hits an F# with delay that sounds cool)

It's hard to hear but at the end of the chord progression there is this little line (the beginning is covered but you can play F#m>D arpeggio):

[Reggae Lick 1]

E|--5-2----------------------5-4------|
B|------3----------2---2-3-5-----5----|
G|--------2----2-4---2-------------4--|
D|------------------------------------|
A|------------------------------------|
E|------------------------------------|


